Description: Fix CVE-2025-22227 - HTTP/2 upgrade stream inherits proper state
 Ensure HTTP/2 upgrade stream inherits proper state from original HTTP/1.1
 connection by copying sent headers/body state. This prevents credentials
 from being leaked during chained redirects when the HTTP client is
 explicitly configured to follow redirects.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/reactor/reactor-netty/commit/522892307ea89bf24fe634e8bfea35728c9bf411
Author: Violeta Georgieva <violetagg@apache.org>
Last-Update: 2025-01-22

